children.subject: As far as I know, CS188 probablyhas the lightest workload of all the CS upper-divs (but the tests can be difficult). There also might be easy CS194s next semester.
Unfortunately, 168 is not offered next semester.... But thanks, Ill consider in my last semester.
CS168 is lighter than 188 imo, at least this semester's iteration of 168

history.content: Hi, guys, I'm a senior transfer students intended for CS major(currently STAT). But I don't have enough time to take CS classes. smoothly(e.g. 2 techs a semester). This semester I'm taking CS70, CS61B(Hilfiger version), and EECS126. I'm planning to take 4 techs next semester. The ones I definitely will take is CS170 and CS184. Can anyone recommend two other very light CS or EE classes that can combine with CS`170 and CS184?  I know it would be horrible to do this no matter what other light CS classes I choose to combine with. But I got no choice. Thank you, guys!
history.subject: The lightest CS class ever recommended, please.
